06/02/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov met with Iraqi Charge d'Affaires Yahya Mahdi on Thursday (5 February) They discussed the situation in Iraq, particularly in Kerbala, where a Bulgarian military contingent is deployed.
Mahdi praised the troops' efforts in bolstering security there.
As for post-war reconstruction, Parvanov pledged Bulgaria's support for the rehabilitation and democratisation of Iraq.
He also voiced hope that Iraq would hold general elections soon, establishing a new legitimate and democratic government.
(BTA, BNR - 05/02/04)
